the following conditions:


1. Irrevocable Original Authorship

1.1 The original author of this Software is Dulsara Pieris. This fact is
permanent, factual, and irrevocable.

1.2 The original author’s credit MUST be preserved in all copies of the
Software, whether modified or unmodified.

1.3 The original author’s credit MUST NOT be removed, altered, minimized,
obscured, replaced, or misrepresented under any circumstances.

1.4 The original author’s credit MUST appear before any other contributor
or modifier credits.

1.5 Any attempt to remove, obscure, downgrade, or misrepresent the original
authorship constitutes a material violation of this license and results in
automatic termination of all granted rights.


2. Mandatory Attribution Placement

2.1 Attribution to the original author MUST appear in ALL of the following:

   a) This LICENSE file  
   b) The README or primary documentation  
   c) An AUTHORS or CREDITS file  

2.2 Attribution MUST ALSO appear in at least one user-accessible surface
if such a surface exists, including but not limited to:

   - CLI output such as --version, --about, or startup messages  
   - An About dialog or settings screen  
   - A splash screen, footer, or visible UI element  
   - Console output on first execution  

2.3 If the Software has no user-visible interface or output, attribution
MUST be included in public documentation, package metadata, or repository
descriptions.

2.4 Lack of a user interface, headless operation, internal use, or backend
deployment SHALL NOT be used as justification to remove or hide attribution.


3. Modification and Modifier Credit

3.1 Any modification, regardless of size or scope, MUST be clearly marked
as a modification.

3.2 Modified versions MUST identify the modifier(s) by name and date of
modification.

3.3 Modifier credit MUST be presented alongside, but never more prominently
than, the original author’s credit.

3.4 Modified versions MUST NOT claim to be the original Software and MUST NOT
imply original authorship by anyone other than the original author.

3.5 Anonymous or pseudonymous modification is NOT permitted for redistribution.


4. Preservation of Authorship History

4.1 AUTHORS, CREDITS, and CHANGELOG files are considered integral parts of
the Software.

4.2 These files MUST be preserved in all redistributions.

4.3 Existing authorship entries MUST NOT be removed, reordered, rewritten,
or reset.

4.4 New contributors or modifiers MAY add entries, but MUST NOT alter or
remove existing historical records.

4.5 Chronological authorship history MUST be maintained.


5. Naming, Identity, and Representation

5.1 Derivative works MUST NOT use the original project name without explicit
written permission from the original author.

5.2 Derivative works MUST include the statement:
"Derived from software originally created by Dulsara Pieris"

5.3 Repository descriptions, package listings, and public distributions
MUST include original author attribution in their descriptions.

5.4 It is strictly prohibited to claim sole authorship, independent creation,
or origin by any party other than the original author.


6. Binary, Obfuscation, and Compilation Protection

6.1 Distribution in compiled, binary, minified, or obfuscated form is
permitted only if all attribution requirements of this license remain fully
accessible.

6.2 Attribution MUST be included in documentation distributed with binaries.

6.3 Removal of attribution through compilation, stripping, compression,
or obfuscation constitutes a license violation.


7. License Continuity and Relicensing

7.1 The Software and all derivative works MUST remain licensed under the
SYNAPSNEX Attribution‑Preserving Source License (SAPL) v1.3.

7.2 Relicensing, sublicensing, or license substitution is NOT permitted.

7.3 Aggregation, wrapping, embedding, or inclusion within larger works does
NOT remove or reduce the obligations of this license.


8. Enforcement, Termination, and Cure

8.1 Any violation of this license automatically terminates all rights granted
under it.

8.2 Rights MAY be reinstated only if:
   a) The violation is fully corrected
   b) All required attribution is restored
   c) Any public misrepresentation is publicly corrected

8.3 Continued use, modification, or distribution after termination
constitutes unauthorized use.


9. AI‑Generated and Automated Derivatives

9.1 Use of the Software, in whole or in part, as training data, reference
material, prompt input, or source material for artificial intelligence,
machine learning systems, code generators, or automated tools is permitted
only if original authorship attribution is preserved.

9.2 Any output, derivative work, or generated content that is substantially
similar to the Software, or that is derived from it through automated or AI‑
assisted processes, SHALL be considered a derivative work under this license.

9.3 Such generated or AI‑assisted derivatives MUST:
   a) Preserve attribution to the original author
   b) Not claim independent creation or invention
   c) Comply with all attribution, naming, and license continuity requirements
      of this license

9.4 Claiming that a work is “AI‑generated”, “machine‑generated”, or
“automatically produced” SHALL NOT be used to remove, bypass, or obscure
original authorship.


